This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new framework for pattern recognition that is different from ordinary supervised learning. It also discusses classification risk and error bounds, which are common topics in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to computer vision (cs.CV) as the proposed framework can be applied to image classification tasks. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses a new approach to learning from labels, which is a fundamental problem in AI. 

Natural language processing (cs.CL) is also a possibility as the paper mentions annotation with complementary labels, which is a common technique in text classification. 

Finally, cybersecurity and cryptography (cs.CR) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper discusses classification risk and error bounds, which are relevant to security applications.
